    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1034"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/29.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister at Mexico
                            City</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Your wire regarding Consul Silliman. Since the second instant I have been
                    urging Foreign Office to take action concerning release Silliman, Marchani and
                    several other Americans imprisoned by order of General Maas. My informant states
                    that Consulate was sacked, all archives taken, Marchani forced by troops to open
                    safe; troops are said to have carried code with them. I feel greatly concerned
                    about the matter and will continue most vigorous efforts to secure release of
                    prisoners and return of code. Will advise you as soon as I ascertain the
                    facts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
